cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.HC

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper analyzes the effects of information overload on online group communication.
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is also likely as the paper discusses the social implications of online communication and how it affects users.
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is a possibility as the paper may provide insights for designing more resilient online communication systems.
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a possibility as the paper analyzes textual features of conversations in the Twitch chat.
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also a possibility as the paper discusses the impact of online communication on user behavior and interaction.
